cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with a supervised multimodal bitransformer model that fuses information from text and image encoders for classification tasks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language) which deals with natural language processing and computational linguistics. The second likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) which deals with image and video analysis. The third likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning) which deals with various machine learning techniques. The fourth likely category is cs.MM (Multimedia) which deals with multimedia analysis and retrieval. The fifth likely category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval) which deals with information retrieval and search engines.
